rk philosophical subtexts; and the mystical-ecstatic poet Zagajewski. A collection of essays representing Anders’s thinking over several decades, Between Fire and Sleep offers a fresh understanding of modern Polish literature and cultural identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPolish literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh1 aGombrowicz, Witold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerbert, Zbigniew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerling-Grudzinski, Gustaw, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKonwicki, Tadeusz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilosz, Czeslaw, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchulz, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzymborska, Wislawa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitkiewicz, Stanislaw Ignacy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZagajewski, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030011167540uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015531040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300155310423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300155310/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY